main event: Three objects in flight from North to South were observed in Menomonee Falls, Wisconsin on 3/2/1964 around 4:10 PM.
interesting points: The objects changed relative position to each other during the 40-60 second observation.
The distance and size of the objects could not be determined.
At first the objects were thought to be birds, but a light source strong enough to reflect off them was not evident.
The case was concluded as UNIDENTIFIED.
There were no photographs or physical evidence obtained.
